The paper proposes a method for learning expressive energy-based policies for continuous states and actions, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also applies the proposed method to learning maximum entropy policies, which is a topic related to reinforcement learning. The experiments involve simulated experiments with swimming and walking robots, which is a topic related to robotics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of amortized Stein variational gradient descent, which is a topic related to control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the experiments involve computer vision tasks, such as object detection and tracking, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
